<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1513" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1513">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/170.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Committee of three appointed by Carranza to examine into
                                circumstances death of Benton arrived here to-day and received later
                                telegraphic instructions to the effect that they should proceed to
                                investigate case with a view to determining whether a disinterment
                                of the body of Benton is necessary or not. It was reported here this
                                afternoon that the committee would probably go to Chihuahua by train
                                to-morrow.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>